 In line with its Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR), Dana Air has donated sundry items to the Lagos Old People’s Home and a number of orphanages across the state. The spokesman of Dana Air, Kingsley Ezenwa, said the donations were in line with the airline’s CSR and philosophy of supporting communities and Non-Governmental Organisations (NGOs) that shared similar objectives. Some of the items donated to the Old People’s Home, Favid Orphanage, and V.O.W (Hope) orphanage were bags of rice, spaghetti, clothes, noodles, toiletries, detergents and beverages.